{
  "texts": [
    "As such, at least one sensor is required in the sensing and perception process, while the arithmetic unit and the controller serve as optional components in HDT, potentially absent in certain instances.The second block explores the construction of the HDT in the digital world, and mainly contains data processing, modeling, simulation and analysis engine.",
    "Data cleaning is using to solve data discontinuity and deletion.",
    "In terms of data storage, the physical world has a corresponding HDT stored in the digital world.",
    "Each of the HDTs has a unique index, which can be used as its ID and can also be used as an account to log in to the HDT.",
    "In addition, as for data fusion and integration, HDT aims to fuse information from these sensors associated with the physical world human representation and to integrate new realtime data with historical data [46]."
  ]
}